title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant 91/30 7.62x54r caliber, 1943
postcontent: This a very nice Mosin Nagant 91/30 battle rifle made at the Izhevsk arsenal in 1943. All serial numbers match including bolt, barrel, mag plate, and butt plate. The gun is shown in the pictures with a new recoil pad, but I have the original butt plate. The gun has had extensive accuracy work. This includes Mojo Peep Sights front and real. I couldn't see the original blade sight, so I changed it out with no drilling or modifications and still have the original front and rear sights that were originally on the gun. Also, I floated the barrel and bedded it in cork to improve barrel harmonics and accuracy. I have killed many deer with this gun. The 7.62x54r cartridge has 3 mm more powder than a 308 cal cartridge. Also, you get two ammo pouches, bayonet, cleaning rod, cleaning/tool kit, two compartment oil cal, and Russian sling. The barrel gas has slight frosting in the grooves, but the lands are shiny and the barrel crown has not been counterbored. This does not seem to affect accuracy as almost all Mosin's have frosting from shooting corrosive ammo during the war.  This is a fine example of history and an accurate gun that is a lot of fun to shoot.
